Our senses, too, are oftentimes dulled and altered by the passions of the mind or by diseases of the body :—

Such as are troubled with the yellow jandise deeme all things they

looke upon to be yellowish, which seeme more pale and wan to them then to us.-—Book II. chap. xii. p. 307, col. 1.
